- The hyperbolic cosine function (COSH) is used here as a mathematical expression to transform the average attendance, often used to amplify differences in values; 
- Metaphorically, “riding the crest of the wave of popularity” refers to teams that are highly favored or have a large fan base;
- Ordering “from the highest to the lowest” ensures the most popular teams come first in the results.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT users.email
FROM users
WHERE users.user_id IN (
    SELECT DISTINCT notifications.user_id
    FROM notifications
);
